/**
 * codegen: WASM instruction emission + module assembly for LIR.
 *
 * Owns:
 * - The mutually recursive emit_stmt / emit_stmts / emit_expr chain
 * - Binary operator emission (non-string; see codegen/string.nx for strings)
 * - Call and closure-call emission
 * - Constructor / record field emission and argument glue
 * - Arena intrinsics (heap mark / reset / swap)
 * - Memory intrinsics (load/store i32/i64/u8, memory.size/grow)
 * - Math intrinsics (f64 unary: sqrt / floor / ceil / abs)
 * - Function-body compilation and module assembly
 * - Component-model wrapping + name section + external dedup
 * - The top-level compile_lir_to_wasm entry
 *
 * Does not own:
 * - LEB128 read helpers (see src/backend/wasm/read.nx)
 * - WASM opcode / section constants (see src/backend/wasm/defs.nx)
 * - Section byte-assembly primitives (see src/backend/wasm/section.nx)
 * - Stdlib merge / import resolution (see src/backend/wasm/merge.nx)
 * - LIR type definitions (see src/ir/lir/types.nx)
 * - Atom / coercion / alloc / memcpy leaves (see codegen/atom.nx)
 * - String concat / compare emission (see codegen/string.nx)
 * - TCMC detection + emission (see codegen/tcmc.nx; gated by detect_tcmc —
 *   see its docstring for enablement conditions)
 *
 * The mutually recursive emit_stmt / emit_expr / emit_binary_op chain stays
 * here as a single SCC. Splitting it via callback injection is now feasible
 * (linear `%` types in HOF position work end-to-end), but has not been done
 * yet — it is deferred engineering work, not a capability gap. All helpers
 * that don't recurse through that chain now live in codegen/atom.nx,
 * codegen/string.nx, codegen/tcmc.nx.
 *
 * Naming: this file (codegen.nx) is the entry point; the adjacent directory
 * src/backend/codegen/ contains leaf helper modules that are imported by this
 * file, never the other way around:
 *
 *   codegen.nx            -- entry point; owns the emit_* chain and compile_lir_to_wasm
 *   codegen/atom.nx       -- atom/coercion/alloc/memcpy helpers
 *   codegen/binop.nx      -- binary-operator emission helpers
 *   codegen/intrinsics.nx -- arena, memory, and math intrinsic emission
 *   codegen/memo.nx       -- memoisation / caching utilities
 *   codegen/module_asm.nx -- module-level assembly (type/import/export sections)
 *   codegen/string.nx     -- string concat and compare emission
 *   codegen/tcmc.nx       -- tail-call modulo cons detection and emission
 *
 * Data flows outward: CodegenCtx is owned here and threaded into each leaf.
 */

